tourBios.carHigh:
2015: A T75 finish at the Nova Scotia Open in July was his only cut made in two starts on the Web.com Tour… In his second PGA TOUR Latinoamérica start, finished T2 at the Abierto Mexicano, one shot back of winner, Justin Hueber. Rounds of 68-68-65-65 produced a 22-under-par effort… In addition to his only top-10 of the year in Latin America, he collected five top-25s, making the cut in 11 of 13 starts to finish 36th on the Order of Merit. 

2014: Finished T79 at Web.com Tour Q-School in December... Played one PGA TOUR Canada event, resulting in a missed cut at the ATB Financial Classic.
tourBios.personal: Supports Putts for Pets charity in his college town of Stillwater, Okla… Favorite city to visit is Kansas City, and his favorite vacation spot is the British Virgin Islands. Top band is Seattle's Minus the Bear… Favorite athlete is Kevin Durant, and he is a big fan of the Indianapolis Colts…Mother, Liz, played college golf at San Jose State…Twitter and Instagram name is @bradgehlosu
